\par }{\b\f28\fs38 Extended variant support in nJudge version 1.7.2. 
\par 
\par By Sergio Lidsell 
\par 
\par }{\i\f29\fs32 
While we're all still waiting for Bruce Duewers article on the Machiavelli endgame play ;-), I am proud to present some of all the great work to extend variant support on the nJudge that has been done since the year 2000 by the kind and untiring coder ext
ra-ordinaire Millis Miller. (A clear cut candidate for the }{\f30\fs32 Don Miller Award for Meritorious Service, }{\i\f29\fs32 in my opinion.) 
\par 
\par This article will focus on the work to release a bugfree (yes, it sure looks like we covered all the bases) Machiavelli implementation and the additional work that has been done to create unambiguous and clear rules. 
\par 
\par For a wealth of information about Machiavelli I unashamedly recommend }{\i\f29\fs32\cf2 The Machiavelli Boardgame Site}{\i\f29\fs32 .
\par 
\par Judges that are known to run nJudge version 1.7.2 at the time of this writing are: USTV, PLTX, NZMB and DEDO. CABC and UFIE will probably follow soon. If you want to see which version of the code a judge runs, send the 'version' command to it. 
\par 
\par The following may be a bit rambling as it was jotted down in all haste. 
\par 
\par }{\b\f28\fs38 Major new features 
\par 
\par }{\f30\fs32 Notice that some of the fixes and features began appearing in 0.8.9. This is a "cumulative" description. The }{\f30\fs32\cf2 Diplomacy Judge Users Manual }{\f30\fs32 contains version info for the new commands. You can also get a }{
\f30\fs32\cf2 detailed version history }{\f30\fs32 for versions newer than 1.1.1. 
\par New improved Machiavelli rules. 
\par Fix of all bugs described in Bruce Duewers article in the }{\f30\fs32\cf2 DPZ F1999M }{\f30\fs32 issue. 
\par Support of 19 Machiavelli scenarios/variants for four (4) to nine (9) players. 
\par Standard map available for Machiavelli play. 
\par Support of Machiavelli 2nd edition with Diplomacy-style control changes. 
\par Support of Basic Classic Machiavelli. 
\par Support of Basic Machiavelli 2nd edition (essentially Diplomacy with a summer season and garrisons). 
\par Possibility to inhibit the use of garrisons in Machiavelli games. 
\par Possibility to remove the summer season from Machiavelli games. 
\par Possibility to add a summer season to Diplomacy games. 
\par Possibility to add coastal convoys to Diplomacy games. 
\par Possibility to disband a unit at any time in Diplomacy games. 
\par Addition of the Diary function. 
\par Machiavelli Game Queue soon available on The Diplomatic Pouch 
\par 
\par }{\b\f28\fs38 Playing Standard Diplomacy with the Machiavelli Maps 
\par 
\par }{\f30\fs32 This is truly one of the most intriguing 
features of the new judge version. Some versions henceforward allow you to disable all Machiavelli features and use the map and setup to play with the standard diplomacy rules. How did this came about? Well as support for Basic and Mach2 was added, the id
ea of adding control of the usage of garrisons and the summer seasons cropped up. And, lo and behold, suddenly you could use the Machiavelli maps for Standard Diplomacy play. 
\par 
\par There is currently a game called "}{\f30\fs32\cf2 Italian}{\f30\fs32 " on }{\f30\fs32\cf2 NZMB }{\f30\fs32 that is awaiting eager playtesters! 
\par 
\par To set up a game this way use these settings: set Mach2, set NoSummer, set NoGarrison, set NoMoney, set NoDice, set NoStorm, set NoDisband, set NoCoastalConvoys. 
\par 
\par }{\b\f28\fs38 Playing "Machiavelli Light" with Diplomacy Style control changes 
\par 
\par }{\f30\fs32 As a way to get 
acquainted with garrison units and an additional summer season this is the way to go. No money, no disasters. In fact none of the much maligned real world simulation features of Mach, just the safe old unchanging Diplomacy tactics. "Me-god" I am beginning
 to hyper-rant, quick, the paper bag... Calm down now, yes calm down, yes. Oomph, that was close. 
\par 
\par To set up a game this way use these settings: set Mach2, set NoMoney, set NoDice, set NoStorm, set Disband, set CoastalConvoys. 
\par 
\par }{\b\f28\fs38 Playing "Machiavelli Light Classic" with continuous control changes 
\par 
\par }{\f30\fs32 And if you feel more daring I recommend you try to master the art of surviving despite your ally suddenly being able to blitz you. 
\par 
\par To set up a game this way use these settings: set NoMach2, set NoMoney, set NoDice, set NoStorm, set Disband, set CoastalConvoys. 
