\par }{\b\f28\fs38 Overview of fixed Machiavelli bugs 
\par 
\par }{\f30\fs32 Below follows an extensive list of the more important known and identified bugs that have been fixed by 1.7.2. 
\par 
\par      First major bugfix was actually version 0.8.7. Support for Machivelli2 rules was added in 0.8.9.
\par      Support for Basic rules in 1.0.0. Fortress support in 1.3.0. Bi-coastal province support (definitively) in 1.5.2. 
\par      Same disaster rolls repeated year after year (Some versions of the judge-such as that still in use on 
\par USEF-got stuck in a pattern where the same famine, plague, etc. rolls occur year after year. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      Negative or out of bounds rolls (This occurred in some versions of the judge code and usually affected income. Often resulted in a power getting a much larger income than it should have. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      Extra special units (Sometimes a player could enter a state where it had more than one special unit. Most often it happened as a result of a bribe. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      Frankenstein's autonomous unit (When unit was made autonomous by a bribe, it would retain the last order given it instead of holding. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      Retreat into city ownership error (This usually occurred when a unit was dislodged and retreated into a garrison. City ownership was erroneously awarded to the power controlling the province and not the garrisoning power. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      3-ducat counter-bribe multiples rule (The player was allowed to enter counter-bribes that were not multiples of three ducats and thus erroneously causing bribes to fail. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      C
onvoy dislodgment (In one case where there was a standoff between an elite fleet and a pair of normal fleets over an area containing a fleet doing a convoy, the convoying fleet was flagged as dislodged (and the convoy thus disrupted) but not listed to ret
reat. The elite and convoying fleets          were owned by the same power. Fixed by 0.8.9.) 
\par      Missing disband order (fixed in 0.8.9) 
\par      Missing units at setup\~ (fixed in 1.2.0) 
\par      Truncated e-mails (this bug also affected non-machiavelli games). 
\par      Victory not detected (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #3}{\f30\fs32 , definitively fixed in 1.3.0) 
\par      Besieged garrison not eliminated on assassination of owner\~(}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #28}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.3.0) 
\par      Maintenance phase ownership\~(}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #43}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.3.0) 
\par      Conversion retreat into rebelling city (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #54}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.3.0) 
\par      Conversion into garrison retreat (Similar to the above. Sometimes a unit was allowed to retreat into the city where the attacker came from.) 
\par      Conversion retreat into Venice city (Similar to the above, but with the added complication of being able to result into two units occupying the same space.) 
\par      Fortress support (added in 1.3.0) 
\par      Straits blocking rules ambiguous and code implementation not correct (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #195}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.5.0). 
\par      Missing city income within bounds check (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #209}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.5.1) 
\par      Coastal restrictions not enforced (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #225}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.5.2) 
\par      Underscore and space in power names problem (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #246}{\f30\fs32 , }{\f30\fs32\cf2 #248}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.5.4) 
\par      Mastr_pt array sizing causing judge crash (}{\f30\fs32\cf2 #303}{\f30\fs32 , fixed in 1.7.0) 
\par 
